Bombus perplexus is a species of bumblebee. 
This particular species is found in North America, specifically in the Rocky Mountains. 
It has a hairy, yellow and black striped body. 
The wings are translucent and the legs are yellow. 
The head has black antennae and a black face. 
This bee plays an important role in pollinating wildflowers and crops. 
Due to habitat loss, the population of Bombus perplexus is considered to be declining.
